Books




Speaking from experience









Douglas Dunn was born in Clydeside, trained as a librarian and worked in the US before moving to Hull, where Larkin became a mentor. In 1967 his first book of poems was hailed by critics as groundbreaking. Two decades later his collection of verse in response to the death of his first wife earned him a wider fame. Nicholas Wroe reports





















Books




Speaking from experience









Douglas Dunn was born in Clydeside, trained as a librarian and worked in the US before moving to Hull, where Larkin became a mentor. In 1967 his first book of poems was hailed by critics as groundbreaking. Two decades later his collection of verse in response to the death of his first wife earned him a wider fame. Nicholas Wroe reports












Share on Facebook









